g.text: UML Diagram: Class Sign in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.

a.title: ― Signifier: Concept whose extension includes perceivable objects.
a.xlink:title: ― Signifier: Concept whose extension includes perceivable objects.

a.title: ― Signified: Concept or object denoted by the signifier associated to a sign.
a.xlink:title: ― Signified: Concept or object denoted by the signifier associated to a sign.

a.title: ― Sign: Something that suggests the presence or existence of a fact, condition, or quality.
a.xlink:title: ― Sign: Something that suggests the presence or existence of a fact, condition, or quality.

a.title: ― ClassificationItem: A space for a category within a statistical classification.
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationItem: A space for a category within a statistical classification.

a.title: ― Datum: Correspondence of a data instance to the concept it represents.
a.xlink:title: ― Datum: Correspondence of a data instance to the concept it represents.

a.title: ― Code: The characters used as a symbol to designate a category within a codelist or classification. (Formally, a sign for which the signifier is non-linguistic alphanumeric string.)
a.xlink:title: ― Code: The characters used as a symbol to designate a category within a codelist or classification. (Formally, a sign for which the signifier is non-linguistic alphanumeric string.)

a.title: ― denotes: Concept or object denoted by the signifier associated to the sign.
a.xlink:title: ― denotes: Concept or object denoted by the signifier associated to the sign.
